A towering, intricate house of cards made from vintage computer server components, circuit boards, and blue-tinted glass panels, dramatically photographed mid-collapse against a deep charcoal background. Some cards are falling away revealing complex interconnected wires and cables beneath, while others still stand precariously balanced. The scene is lit with dramatic side lighting creating sharp shadows, photographed in the style of high-end product photography with shallow depth of field. Small glowing indicator lights dot the structure in amber and blue, suggesting the systems were still active. The composition emphasizes both the impressive complexity of what was built and the chaos of dismantling something so interconnected.
